{
  "_description": "RECON DOMLogger++ config (attack-surface mapping, corrected). IDENTICAL hooks+alerts to the hunt config, but the global '*' canary match is neutralized to log EVERY sink hit ('exec:return /.*/'). Keyword/canary/-SANTAG per-sink gates and the clobber requiredHooks gate are relaxed to log-all so you see the full surface; structural exec gates (timer string-arg, setAttribute danger-name, meta-refresh, style url(), XSS_DOM node-type) are kept because they define what the sink captures. The GLOBAL !match/!matchTrace denoise list is kept. Same unhookable-sink removals and instance-path opener fix as the hunt config. Use this FIRST to enumerate which sinks the app exercises, then switch to the hunt config (canary-gated) to hunt.",
